INSTALL - textmachine
=====================

All libraries can be installed via the Arduino IDE Library Manager:
  Sketch > Include Library > Manage Libraries

REQUIRED LIBRARIES
------------------

1. Adafruit GFX Library
   - Author: Adafruit
   - Search: "Adafruit GFX"
   - Contains : Fonts/FreeSans9pt7b.h , Fonts/FreeSansBold9pt7b.h, as well

2. Adafruit ILI9341
   - Author: Adafruit
   - Search: "Adafruit ILI9341"

3. MKRNB
   - Author: Arduino
   - Search: "MKRNB"

HARDWARE
--------
- Arduino MKR NB 1500
- ILI9341 SPI display
- FT6336U capacitive touchscreen (I2C, address 0x38)
- SIM card with SMS capability (tested on Tello / T-Mobile NB-IoT)
- Antenna tuned for LTE Band 12 (700 MHz)

BUILT-IN LIBRARIES (no install needed)
---------------------------------------
- SPI      (included with Arduino IDE)
- Wire     (included with Arduino IDE)
- Math     (included with Arduino IDE)

NOTES
-----
- Make sure your SIM card supports NB-IoT or LTE-M (Cat-M1)
- Select "Arduino MKR NB 1500" as your board in the IDE
- Board package: "Arduino SAMD Boards" via Boards Manager
